WEBVTT

00:02.349 --> 00:03.813
What Are You Afraid Of?

00:04.550 --> 00:07.511
Cowards die many times before their deaths.

00:07.905 --> 00:10.569
The valiant never taste of death but once.

00:11.082 --> 00:13.543
Of all the wonders that I yet have heard,...

00:13.965 --> 00:16.924
...It seems to me most strange that men should fear;...

00:17.243 --> 00:19.524
...Seeing that death, a necessary end,...

00:19.790 --> 00:21.507
...Will come when it will come.

00:22.221 --> 00:26.897
In Julius Caesar (1599) written by William Shakespeare...

00:28.227 --> 00:32.191
"People living deeply have no fear of death."  - Anais Nin

00:32.886 --> 00:37.857
"Only when we are no longer afraid do we begin to live." - Dorothy Thompson

00:38.460 --> 00:44.139
"Don't be afraid to go out on a limb. That's where the fruit is." - H. Jackson Browne

00:44.897 --> 00:51.001
"Too many people are thinking of security instead of opportunity." - James F. Bymes

00:51.567 --> 00:56.796
"Nothing in life is to be feared. It is only to be understood." - Marie Curie

00:57.485 --> 01:03.717
"Ultimately we know deeply that the other side of every fear is a freedom." - Marilyn Ferguson

01:04.529 --> 01:07.595
"You can judge your age by the amount of pain you feel...

01:07.819 --> 01:11.747
... when you come in contact with a new idea. - Pearl S. Buck

01:12.485 --> 01:16.767
"Worry gives a small thing a big shadow." - Swedish Proverb

